#pythontip by @PyPrinciples:

You can use | and &amp; for set union and intersection. 

&gt;&gt;&gt; {1, 2} &amp; {2, 3}
{2}
&gt;&gt;&gt; {1, 2} | {2, 3}
{1, 2, 3}

&gt;&gt;&gt; {True: 'yes', 1: 'no', 1.0: 'maybe'}
{True: 'maybe'}

