#python3

Inverting a dictionary:
&gt;&gt;&gt; my_map = { 'a': 1, 'b': 2}
&gt;&gt;&gt; inv_map = {v: k for k, v in my_map.items()}
&gt;&gt;&gt; inv_map
{1: 'a', 2: 'b'}
#python

Add elements of one dictionary to another with the update() method:

&gt;&gt;&gt; d1 = {'a' : 1, "b" : 2}
&gt;&gt;&gt; d2 = {'c' : 2, "d" : 42, "a" : 3}
&gt;&gt;&gt; d1.update(d2)
&gt;&gt;&gt; d1
{'a': 3, 'b': 2, 'c': 2, 'd': 42}

