#pythontip from @daviddelachurch
Loving #Python3.5 PEP 448 for overwriting a dictionary of default values:

&gt;&gt;&gt; defaults = {"lenny": "white", "carl": "black"}
&gt;&gt;&gt; overwrite = {"lenny": "yellow"}
&gt;&gt;&gt; new = {**defaults, **overwrite}
&gt;&gt;&gt; new
{'lenny': 'yellow', 'carl': 'black'}

